# Allowlist for benign redirects lychee would otherwise report under
# the weekly link-check run. This file is NOT a wildcard silence —
# every entry is a specific URL whose redirect or inaccessibility is
# expected and documented. Add a `# why:` comment above each entry.
#
# Format: one regular expression per line (lychee uses the `regex`
# crate; plain strings match as substrings).

# why: GitHub's security-advisories-new page redirects to /login when
# lychee hits it unauthenticated, because creating an advisory
# requires a signed-in session with repo admin. The final status is
# 200 OK via the login page. This URL is referenced from SECURITY.md
# as the canonical private-disclosure entry point; it doesn't move.
^https://github\.com/apet97/go-clockify/security/advisories/new$
